WEBVTT

00:06.484 --> 00:06.789
.

00:06.832 --> 00:09.183
- Previously on "Shooter"...

00:09.226 --> 00:10.401
- We're looking for educated
men like you to help us out.

00:10.445 --> 00:11.750
You interested?
- Yes, sir.

00:11.794 --> 00:13.187
- I always wanted
to meet one of you.

00:13.230 --> 00:14.536
- Russo has a long memory.

00:14.579 --> 00:16.320
- Russo's location,
I let you live.

00:16.364 --> 00:18.322
- Yeah, maybe.
Russo won't.

00:18.366 --> 00:20.368
- I wanted to be the first one
to officially welcome you

00:20.411 --> 00:22.544
to the family.
- This family have a name?

00:22.587 --> 00:24.328
- You worked
with Atlas for years.

00:24.372 --> 00:26.069
What's their endgame?

00:26.113 --> 00:28.680
- What's the final check on
absolute power in government?

00:28.724 --> 00:30.073
- The Supreme Court.

00:30.117 --> 00:32.206
- Control that,
control everything.

00:32.249 --> 00:33.598
[grunts]

00:33.642 --> 00:35.383
- The confirmation's already
on the calendar.

00:35.426 --> 00:38.081
This is happening.
- There may be another problem.

00:38.125 --> 00:40.562
Earl Swagger's evidence
might be in play too.

00:40.605 --> 00:42.520
- After you left yesterday,
Bama came by.

00:42.564 --> 00:45.436
Said we need to drop the
wrongful death suit or else.

00:45.480 --> 00:47.134
- Get in there.

00:47.177 --> 00:48.613
[rumbling]

00:48.657 --> 00:50.180
I want that card intact.

00:50.224 --> 00:51.703
Swagger, I will
take either way.

00:51.747 --> 00:53.444
- Door was open.

00:53.488 --> 00:55.707
- We're not interested
in Daddy's money, Junior.

00:55.751 --> 00:57.144
- [grunting]

00:57.187 --> 00:59.581
- Piece of shit!
- [grunts]

00:59.624 --> 01:01.365
- Sam.
[line trills]

01:01.409 --> 01:02.801
- 911. What's your emergency?

01:02.845 --> 01:05.108
- Hi, I need
an ambulance right now.

01:12.376 --> 01:15.292
- I'm not exactly sure
where to begin,

01:15.336 --> 01:18.861
except to say that I'm
doing this for my wife and son.

01:18.904 --> 01:20.863
I need...

01:23.170 --> 01:26.216
To set the record straight.

01:26.260 --> 01:29.219
[heart monitor beeping]

01:29.263 --> 01:32.222
[dramatic music]

01:32.266 --> 01:39.360
♪

01:40.622 --> 01:41.840
- Hey.

01:41.884 --> 01:49.109
♪

01:50.458 --> 01:52.416
- [sighs]

01:52.460 --> 01:56.377
♪

01:56.420 --> 01:57.813
I cannot wait
to get my hands on him.

01:57.856 --> 01:59.597
- Look, he's--
he's just gonna run.

01:59.641 --> 02:01.556
You know that, right?
- Then he's gonna die tired.

02:01.599 --> 02:03.253
- Okay, if Junior falls
from a long gun,

02:03.297 --> 02:06.169
you'll be in jail before
his heart stops beating.

02:06.213 --> 02:07.562
- The guy's a piece
of human garbage.

02:07.605 --> 02:10.217
He's not even worth a bullet.

02:10.260 --> 02:11.609
I got a plan.

02:11.653 --> 02:14.699
- Hey...don't get caught.

02:14.743 --> 02:17.702
[tense music]

02:17.746 --> 02:24.666
♪

02:40.812 --> 02:43.815
[heartbeat thumping]

02:50.518 --> 02:55.697
♪

02:55.740 --> 02:57.742
[touch-tones beeping]

02:57.786 --> 03:00.223
[line trills]

03:00.267 --> 03:03.357
- Hey, you might want
to get over to Bama Cattle.

03:03.400 --> 03:05.315
I think someone's about to die.

03:05.359 --> 03:08.710
♪

03:08.753 --> 03:10.494
- We're closed.

03:11.756 --> 03:14.281
[grunts]

03:14.324 --> 03:17.545
♪

03:17.588 --> 03:19.895
- Get lost, Swagger.

03:19.938 --> 03:21.853
- [grunts]
[gunshot]

03:21.897 --> 03:25.770
[man grunting and coughing]

03:25.814 --> 03:29.774
♪

03:29.818 --> 03:30.862
- [grunts]

03:30.906 --> 03:33.430
- Sam Vincent is an old man.

03:33.474 --> 03:34.866
You like beating up on old men?

03:34.910 --> 03:36.868
Huh?
I'm old. Take a shot at me!

03:36.912 --> 03:38.348
- I don't know what the hell
you're talking about.

03:38.392 --> 03:40.698
I didn't touch anybody.
- [grunts]

03:40.742 --> 03:43.266
Lie to me again!
- Go to hell.

03:43.310 --> 03:44.702
[both grunting]

03:44.746 --> 03:47.488
- I got a better idea.
You run this place.

03:47.531 --> 03:50.317
You know what a bone saw
would do to a man's arm!

03:50.360 --> 03:51.840
- Please, stop! Stop!

03:51.883 --> 03:53.711
- What did you want from Sam?
- Stop, please!

03:53.755 --> 03:55.365
- I'll stop when you tell me.

03:55.409 --> 03:56.801
- He has something
that belongs to my dad!

03:56.845 --> 03:58.238
Evidence!
He has evidence!

03:58.281 --> 04:00.849
[gunshot]
- Ah!

04:00.892 --> 04:03.286
Now, you're fast, Swagger,
but you're not this fast.

04:03.330 --> 04:04.853
Drop the gun--now.

04:04.896 --> 04:08.465
♪

04:08.509 --> 04:09.684
[gun clatters]

04:09.727 --> 04:11.555
You okay, son?
- Yeah.

04:11.599 --> 04:14.602
- Now, you couldn't have picked
a worse spot to do this.

04:14.645 --> 04:17.735
That grinder over there,
that thing cost me a mint.

04:17.779 --> 04:19.911
But, damn, is it a powerhouse.

04:19.955 --> 04:21.826
They wouldn't even
find your DNA.

04:21.870 --> 04:25.787
♪

04:25.830 --> 04:28.659
- Got an anonymous call
about some boys

04:28.703 --> 04:31.923
working out their problems.
- I want Swagger arrested.

04:31.967 --> 04:33.403
- On what charge?

04:33.447 --> 04:36.319
- Trespassing,
assault with a deadly weapon,

04:36.363 --> 04:39.017
attempted murder,
being an asshole.

04:39.061 --> 04:40.758
- Well, that last one
ain't even a crime.

04:40.802 --> 04:44.501
- [chuckles]
- And as for the rest of it,

04:44.545 --> 04:46.068
looks like your boy tripped.

04:46.111 --> 04:48.462
Bob Lee was helping him up.

04:48.505 --> 04:51.595
- Cut the shit, Brown.

04:51.639 --> 04:55.338
- That's Sheriff Brown, Red.

04:55.382 --> 04:59.299
And if I say there's no crime,
there's no crime.

05:00.343 --> 05:02.954
Unless you want your boy
to come down to the station,

05:02.998 --> 05:06.088
talk to me about what happened
to Sam Vincent.

05:06.131 --> 05:09.961
♪

05:10.005 --> 05:11.572
- [sighs]

05:11.615 --> 05:15.750
We have no idea what
you're talking about, Sheriff.

05:15.793 --> 05:20.102
- Maybe, maybe not.
Either way, we'll be in touch.

05:20.145 --> 05:22.017
Let's go, Bob Lee.

05:22.060 --> 05:27.762
♪

05:27.805 --> 05:29.894
- There's a pale horse
coming for you, Bama.

05:29.938 --> 05:32.419
- I ain't scared of you.

05:32.462 --> 05:33.855
- Yeah, you are.

05:33.898 --> 05:36.336
Or else you wouldn't be here.

05:36.379 --> 05:39.469
♪

05:39.513 --> 05:42.472
[dramatic music]

05:42.516 --> 05:49.566
♪

05:51.655 --> 05:52.047
.

05:52.090 --> 05:53.918
- You just gonna
let Swagger go?

05:53.962 --> 05:55.311
He knows about the tapes.

05:55.355 --> 05:56.530
- Oh, shut your hole.

05:56.573 --> 05:58.314
Did I raise a fool?

05:58.358 --> 06:01.404
You think that you can put
Sam Vincent in the hospital

06:01.448 --> 06:05.190
and not draw return fire?
- You told me to handle it.

06:05.234 --> 06:08.890
- Not by trying to kill the man
who raised Bob Lee Swagger.

06:08.933 --> 06:10.370
God damn it.

06:10.413 --> 06:12.241
If you weren't already
beat to shit,

06:12.284 --> 06:14.591
I swear I would give you
a thrashing myself.

06:14.635 --> 06:17.159
- I wanted to help you.
- You want to help?

06:17.202 --> 06:19.379
Forget the rest of your shit.
We're leaving now.

06:27.343 --> 06:30.172
- Hope you brought doughnuts.
- Not with this ass.

06:30.215 --> 06:32.087
- We need to come up
with a plan.

06:32.130 --> 06:34.132
- For the 100th time,
call your new friend

06:34.176 --> 06:36.265
at Justice, Margo,
and we work out

06:36.308 --> 06:38.223
some kind
of protective custody deal.

06:38.267 --> 06:41.401
- Why, you thinking about
a nice town house in Arizona?

06:41.444 --> 06:44.055
- I mean,
Flagstaff has a vibe.

06:44.099 --> 06:46.014
- We're not calling
Margo or anyone.

06:46.057 --> 06:47.407
If the chief of staff is Atlas,

06:47.450 --> 06:49.191
then the president
could be in it too.

06:49.234 --> 06:50.453
We don't have any friends.

06:50.497 --> 06:51.976
- If Isaac's right,
then--then yeah,

06:52.020 --> 06:53.543
we are running out of options.

06:53.587 --> 06:55.197
If the president's involved,
it's a game changer, right?

06:55.240 --> 06:57.199
We can't get him.
- Anyone is gettable.

06:57.242 --> 06:59.593
- Going after the president
is a good way to get dead.

06:59.636 --> 07:01.508
- And I told you I'm not gonna
stop until I have them all.

07:01.551 --> 07:03.335
- Okay, before you guys
start planning

07:03.379 --> 07:05.425
another presidential
assassination,

07:05.468 --> 07:08.558
um, I've been going through
Patricia's burn files.

07:08.602 --> 07:11.474
Maybe we can squeeze Gold
to get to Atlas.

07:11.518 --> 07:13.911
Chief of staff to the president
is not gonna want that

07:13.955 --> 07:15.043
getting out into the world.

07:15.086 --> 07:16.218
- It's a start.

07:16.261 --> 07:18.350
- No, it's another
sack-of-shit idea.

07:18.394 --> 07:20.309
You go direct at Gold,
it exposes us,

07:20.352 --> 07:22.006
and we get zero in return.

07:22.050 --> 07:25.575
- I'm open to other options
but not running.

07:25.619 --> 07:27.142
- So you ready to risk it?

07:27.185 --> 07:30.232
- You and I aren't
risking anything.

07:30.275 --> 07:32.364
Harris just volunteered
for the job.

07:32.408 --> 07:33.931
- Wait, what?

07:35.106 --> 07:36.368
- [groans]

07:36.412 --> 07:37.674
June come with you?

07:37.718 --> 07:39.546
[heart monitor beeping]

07:39.589 --> 07:42.026
- What?

07:42.070 --> 07:46.944
- She promised to bring those
mashed potatoes I like.

07:46.988 --> 07:48.424
Extra gravy.
- No, no, no, no.

07:48.468 --> 07:52.907
I'm not Earl, Sam.
It's Bob Lee.

07:52.950 --> 07:54.430
You're in the hospital.

07:54.474 --> 07:57.433
- I should have listened
to you, Earl.

07:57.477 --> 08:00.001
I should have seen the truth.

08:00.044 --> 08:03.700
I didn't have to go over there
and fight like you did.

08:03.744 --> 08:07.051
Couldn't understand
why you'd want to...

08:07.095 --> 08:09.314
tell everyone what happened.

08:11.273 --> 08:14.450
- Police gave me
Sam's things.

08:14.494 --> 08:15.973
- What's going on with him?

08:16.017 --> 08:17.975
- He's been in and out all day.
Why?

08:18.019 --> 08:19.455
What'd he say to you?

08:19.499 --> 08:21.196
- He thinks I'm my dad, and--

08:21.239 --> 08:22.458
[device beeps]

08:22.502 --> 08:24.286
There's something on in there.

08:25.592 --> 08:27.507
What is it?

08:27.550 --> 08:29.987
- Don't know.
I think it's his tape recorder.

08:32.163 --> 08:34.601
- Batteries still work?
[tape recorder clicks]

08:34.644 --> 08:36.516
- Oh, you should have
played ball, old man.

08:36.559 --> 08:37.560
Swaggers ain't worth
dying over.

08:37.604 --> 08:38.605
- This is--
- Junior.

08:38.648 --> 08:40.345
- I want Earl's evidence,

08:40.389 --> 08:42.260
and I want it now.
- Go ahead and kill me.

08:42.304 --> 08:44.698
It'll prove how much of
an idiot Red's got for a son.

08:44.741 --> 08:48.484
- [grunting]

08:48.528 --> 08:50.747
[tape recorder clicks]

08:50.791 --> 08:54.011
- Junior mentioned something
about this when I saw him.

08:54.055 --> 08:55.491
Brown's gotta hear this.

08:55.535 --> 08:57.319
- I mean, what evidence
is he talking about?

08:57.362 --> 08:58.755
- I don't know.

08:58.799 --> 09:00.322
- Will you folks
be needing dinner?

09:00.365 --> 09:01.584
The cafeteria's closing soon.

09:01.628 --> 09:03.325
- No, we're good.
Thank you.

09:03.368 --> 09:05.588
[ominous music]

09:05.632 --> 09:07.242
- I'm--I'm just gonna call him,

09:07.285 --> 09:09.374
see if he can come by.

09:09.418 --> 09:12.987
- There's a secret group that
used to be called Phoenix,

09:13.030 --> 09:15.729
but it goes by
a different name now.

09:15.772 --> 09:18.645
Atlas.

09:18.688 --> 09:21.517
I helped start it.

09:21.561 --> 09:25.173
And for that, I am sorry.

09:25.216 --> 09:28.089
But I'm also guilty...

09:28.132 --> 09:31.701
and will accept whatever
punishment comes my way.

09:31.745 --> 09:35.226
In the event of my death...

09:35.270 --> 09:37.664
consider this my affidavit.

09:37.707 --> 09:39.622
- We expect minimal
resistance here,

09:39.666 --> 09:41.581
north of Du Song.

09:41.624 --> 09:43.539
- Looks pretty far in,
Ms. Mayfield.

09:43.583 --> 09:45.410
- Yes.

09:45.454 --> 09:48.239
We'll helo drop you here,
meet the supply shipment here,

09:48.283 --> 09:51.068
and shut it down.
- What are they shipping?

09:51.112 --> 09:53.375
- Weapons.
Mostly stolen.

09:53.418 --> 09:55.420
They've been running them
to the Vietcong.

09:55.464 --> 09:57.640
This line's been operational
for two years.

09:57.684 --> 10:00.556
We're gonna intercede.
- All right.

10:05.561 --> 10:08.085
- Ma'am.
- This is Major Raymond Brooks.

10:08.129 --> 10:10.044
Detachment A-101,
Company C,

10:10.087 --> 10:12.220
5th Special Forces Group.
- [scoffs]

10:12.263 --> 10:15.179
No offense, you seem
a little young to be a major.

10:15.223 --> 10:17.660
How long you been in country?
- Since '68, Sergeant.

10:17.704 --> 10:19.314
Battle of Lang Vei.

10:19.357 --> 10:20.794
- Surprised you would want
to be in Cambodia,

10:20.837 --> 10:23.231
considering, uh,
they refused to fight.

10:23.274 --> 10:26.147
- Oh, unfortunately, we don't
get to choose our friends.

10:26.190 --> 10:28.149
- I'll fill you in
over dinner, Major.

10:28.192 --> 10:30.412
- Uh, we haven't
discussed the target.

10:31.761 --> 10:34.459
- I told you:
the supply line.

10:34.503 --> 10:35.678
- Yeah, but who's running it?
How many men?

10:35.722 --> 10:37.288
What side of the fence?

10:37.332 --> 10:40.378
- When I have that information,
you'll have it.

10:40.422 --> 10:42.772
- With all due respect,
Ms. Mayfield,

10:42.816 --> 10:44.687
we've had some good luck.

10:44.731 --> 10:46.210
We've run some good missions.

10:46.254 --> 10:47.385
But now's not the time
to get cocky.

10:47.429 --> 10:48.691
- Sergeant,
it's my understanding

10:48.735 --> 10:51.259
that Ms. Mayfield plans it
and you execute.

10:51.302 --> 10:52.739
Your group has been
extremely effective,

10:52.782 --> 10:54.436
but that means
the enemy adapts.

10:54.479 --> 10:57.700
It's harder for us to get
good intel, but we will.

10:57.744 --> 11:00.268
Understood?

11:00.311 --> 11:01.661
- Understood.

11:01.704 --> 11:04.664
[tense music]

11:04.707 --> 11:06.535
♪

11:06.578 --> 11:08.232
I should have known then.

11:08.276 --> 11:09.886
When they don't
tell you the target,

11:09.930 --> 11:12.759
it's because they don't
want you to know the target.

11:14.325 --> 11:16.719
And for some reason,
bad news always seems

11:16.763 --> 11:18.721
to come with the new guy.

11:18.765 --> 11:21.724
[dramatic music]

11:21.768 --> 11:28.818
♪

11:34.694 --> 11:38.567
- Nuclear waste?
This place safe for us?

11:38.610 --> 11:41.222
- Safest place you'll ever be,

11:41.265 --> 11:44.312
especially with Swagger
after you.

11:44.355 --> 11:46.662
We call it the Campus.

11:46.706 --> 11:53.669
♪

11:53.713 --> 11:55.845
- [sighs]

11:55.889 --> 11:57.760
We the only ones here?

11:57.804 --> 11:59.370
- Not quite.

12:00.894 --> 12:03.331
- My God.

12:03.374 --> 12:05.768
I can't believe it.
I'm finally in.

12:05.812 --> 12:07.248
- [chuckles]

12:07.291 --> 12:08.379
Well, you're on the doorstep,
son.

12:08.423 --> 12:10.164
You haven't entered yet.

12:10.207 --> 12:13.341
And if you do, know this.

12:13.384 --> 12:15.778
That door is one-way.

12:15.822 --> 12:17.780
Now, they'll get you
squared away,

12:17.824 --> 12:19.651
find you a place to wash up.

12:19.695 --> 12:22.872
And listen to me, now.
This is important.

12:22.916 --> 12:26.920
You are nobody here.
Do not ask questions.

12:26.963 --> 12:29.618
Do not act entitled.
- Dad, I--

12:29.661 --> 12:33.361
- Your dad was left
outside those gates.

12:33.404 --> 12:35.885
Now, you follow orders here,
you'll do just fine.

12:35.929 --> 12:37.539
I'll see you later.

12:37.582 --> 12:40.324
♪

12:40.368 --> 12:41.586
- [chuckles softly]

12:44.720 --> 12:45.068
.

12:45.112 --> 12:47.027
- All they had downstairs.

12:47.070 --> 12:48.289
- Ten grand a day,
and the food is better

12:48.332 --> 12:49.856
in a gas station.

12:49.899 --> 12:52.119
You didn't happen to see
any whiskey down there?

12:52.162 --> 12:54.077
- I don't think
whiskey's gonna help you.

12:54.121 --> 12:58.212
- Oh, whiskey always helps.
That's the secret.

12:59.561 --> 13:02.433
How long you been here?
- Since Julie called.

13:04.000 --> 13:05.523
Why didn't you tell me?

13:05.567 --> 13:07.221
About your tumor?

13:07.264 --> 13:10.224
- Oh, hell, what difference
would it make?

13:10.267 --> 13:12.400
So you'd look at me like
you're looking at me right now?

13:12.443 --> 13:14.097
No, thanks.

13:14.141 --> 13:16.534
- You're one tough old bastard,
you know that?

13:16.578 --> 13:18.623
- You would have done
the same thing.

13:21.931 --> 13:23.628
Spit it out, son.

13:25.630 --> 13:27.937
- I'm sorry to do it now.

13:30.461 --> 13:32.681
But do you have any idea
what Junior was looking for?

13:32.724 --> 13:34.596
He said something
about evidence.

13:34.639 --> 13:36.337
- Oh, hell, he makes
about as much sense

13:36.380 --> 13:38.208
as a bleating goat.

13:38.252 --> 13:42.343
- Sam, what did he
want from you?

13:44.649 --> 13:46.695
- It was a long time ago.

13:46.738 --> 13:50.481
- Well, it's important
to the Bamas now.

13:50.525 --> 13:52.266
- I don't have
to tell you how horrific

13:52.309 --> 13:55.573
the war in Vietnam was.

13:55.617 --> 13:59.316
Your daddy got caught up
in some bad stuff over there.

13:59.360 --> 14:03.146
Wanted to talk about
some of the things he saw.

14:03.190 --> 14:05.627
Things he lied about
at the time.

14:05.670 --> 14:07.368
- Why would the Bamas care?

14:07.411 --> 14:09.587
- Don't know.

14:09.631 --> 14:12.460
But there were
congressional hearings.

14:12.503 --> 14:14.462
They were classified.

14:14.505 --> 14:15.724
[soft dramatic music]

14:15.767 --> 14:17.987
- Did he ever
end up testifying?

14:18.031 --> 14:21.208
♪

14:21.251 --> 14:23.340
- Thought I was helping him.

14:23.384 --> 14:25.255
- So you told him not to talk.

14:25.299 --> 14:27.475
- I was worried if he
went through with it,

14:27.518 --> 14:29.303
it'd bring it all back up.

14:29.346 --> 14:32.393
Had to think about you
and your mama.

14:32.436 --> 14:36.484
Said he made a video,
sort of a confession.

14:36.527 --> 14:40.270
Kept it locked away somewhere.
I never did see it.

14:40.314 --> 14:44.144
Probably just dust by now.

14:44.187 --> 14:46.450
- Yeah, Gutierrez
was right.

14:46.494 --> 14:49.366
Atlas killed my dad 'cause
he was gonna rat them out.

14:49.410 --> 14:52.674
They used the affair with Edie
as motive for Jimmy Poole,

14:52.717 --> 14:54.806
helped him escape,
set up the meet,

14:54.850 --> 14:56.330
and then put a sniper
on long gun

14:56.373 --> 14:58.114
to make sure
the job got done.

14:58.158 --> 15:00.029
- Your daddy's confession

15:00.073 --> 15:02.684
is incriminating evidence
of their crimes.

15:02.727 --> 15:04.991
- I gotta find it.

15:05.034 --> 15:06.818
- Jesus, Red,
if I didn't know better,

15:06.862 --> 15:10.561
I'd say you turned stupid
or careless.

15:10.605 --> 15:12.476
- You know I'm not either
of those things.

15:12.520 --> 15:15.262
- Then why don't you
have the card?

15:15.305 --> 15:17.090
- I know its location.

15:17.133 --> 15:18.787
Just need a plan to get
our hands on it.

15:18.830 --> 15:22.182
- You spent 20 hours dragging
your son across the country--

15:22.225 --> 15:25.359
time that could have been spent
pulling together the plan.

15:25.402 --> 15:27.796
- I had to get him
away from Swagger.

15:27.839 --> 15:31.495
He made a mistake.
- No shit. Capital M.

15:31.539 --> 15:33.323
And now Swagger's
on high alert.

15:33.367 --> 15:35.108
He knows about
his father's evidence.

15:35.151 --> 15:38.067
- We haven't found
that evidence in 30 years.

15:38.111 --> 15:41.462
He ain't gonna find it either.
Don't worry about Swagger.

15:41.505 --> 15:44.117
- You said something similar
when we framed him

15:44.160 --> 15:46.597
for the Ukrainian president
hit.

15:46.641 --> 15:48.382
How'd that work out?

15:48.425 --> 15:52.386
The Swagger family
is personal to you, Red.

15:53.387 --> 15:55.519
- Earl was
a moralistic asshole

15:55.563 --> 15:58.740
who acted like
his shit didn't stink.

15:58.783 --> 16:00.394
He was the sheriff
of a small town

16:00.437 --> 16:01.786
that wouldn't have existed

16:01.830 --> 16:04.180
if it hadn't been for me
and the work I did.

16:04.224 --> 16:07.314
- Meaning
he wouldn't be bought.

16:07.357 --> 16:11.579
Of course, we knew about your
troubles expanding Bama Cattle.

16:11.622 --> 16:13.537
A lot of those farmers
didn't want to sell,

16:13.581 --> 16:16.453
and they had Sheriff Swagger
on their side.

16:16.497 --> 16:18.890
[tense music]

16:18.934 --> 16:21.850
- But you made that problem
go away, didn't you?

16:21.893 --> 16:23.286
- Hmm.

16:23.330 --> 16:24.853
- And I am just so thankful

16:24.896 --> 16:27.508
that I could be of service.

16:27.551 --> 16:29.510
- I should have
seen this coming.

16:29.553 --> 16:32.513
You let it get personal,
you make mistakes.

16:32.556 --> 16:35.255
And mistakes are fatal--

16:35.298 --> 16:37.909
usually for the one
making them.

16:37.953 --> 16:43.611
♪

16:43.654 --> 16:46.309
- You'll have the president's
pick for the chief justice

16:46.353 --> 16:47.658
this afternoon.

16:47.702 --> 16:50.792
Thank you.
[reporters clamoring]

16:52.315 --> 16:54.535
Hi. Thank you.
Thank you for coming.

16:54.578 --> 16:56.798
[indistinct chatter]

16:56.841 --> 16:59.627
- [clears throat]
Mr. Gold. Hi.

16:59.670 --> 17:01.150
- I know you.

17:01.194 --> 17:03.370
- Uh, no, we've actually
never officially met.

17:03.413 --> 17:05.633
- You're Hayes'
legislative aide.

17:05.676 --> 17:07.374
- Well, was.
- Mm.

17:07.417 --> 17:09.463
- I need a minute of your time.

17:09.506 --> 17:12.640
- That is one thing
I don't have.

17:12.683 --> 17:13.902
- About the Alpha Boys.

17:18.167 --> 17:19.516
- Clock's ticking.

17:19.560 --> 17:21.170
- I'll be super quick.

17:21.214 --> 17:23.825
Uh, the Alpha Boys are
a white nationalist group, uh,

17:23.868 --> 17:25.435
dressed up to look
like a legitimate

17:25.479 --> 17:27.176
political organization--
- I know who they are.

17:27.220 --> 17:28.743
- Great.
Uh, so I've been doing

17:28.786 --> 17:33.443
some research for my new job,
and, um, long story short,

17:33.487 --> 17:36.838
I-I, uh, figured out
who founded the Alpha Boys.

17:36.881 --> 17:38.579
You.

17:38.622 --> 17:41.538
$13,000 wire transfer
start-up money there

17:41.582 --> 17:43.279
to establish
a headquarters, uh,

17:43.323 --> 17:45.673
start getting the message out--
bots, targeted ads.

17:45.716 --> 17:46.935
Social media
makes it a lot easier

17:46.978 --> 17:48.676
to be a racist these days.

17:48.719 --> 17:50.373
- [chuckles]

17:50.417 --> 17:52.332
Gregson's famous gossip files.

17:52.375 --> 17:54.682
The NSA's own J. Edgar,
except that she wore

17:54.725 --> 17:56.336
her dresses in public.

17:56.379 --> 17:57.902
I always wondered
who found these.

17:57.946 --> 17:59.600
Thanks for letting me know.

18:00.688 --> 18:02.733
- Whatever you're planning
on doing, stop.

18:04.953 --> 18:06.520
- You're gonna have to be
a little more specific.

18:06.563 --> 18:09.305
Uh, I've got
a pretty full plate.

18:09.349 --> 18:10.393
- Atlas.
- What?

18:10.437 --> 18:11.655
- You heard me.

18:11.699 --> 18:12.917
If you don't get Atlas to stop

18:12.961 --> 18:15.006
whatever event
they're planning,

18:15.050 --> 18:17.661
this all goes public.

18:17.705 --> 18:20.186
- Okay, you want to, uh,
go public with that,

18:20.229 --> 18:21.578
be my guest.

18:21.622 --> 18:22.710
There's a bunch of reporters
ten feet away.

18:22.753 --> 18:26.192
Hey, Phil.

18:26.235 --> 18:28.585
I think they'll
probably just shrug.

18:28.629 --> 18:31.414
I support a lot of groups.
None of them are illegal.

18:31.458 --> 18:33.286
A lot more important things
going on in the world.

18:33.329 --> 18:35.853
Hey, take a look at this,
uh, Phil.

18:35.897 --> 18:37.377
And call me later.

18:37.420 --> 18:38.856
I'll answer any
questions you have.

18:38.900 --> 18:41.250
♪

18:41.294 --> 18:43.818
Don't ever try
to blackmail anyone.

18:43.861 --> 18:45.385
You suck at it.

18:45.428 --> 18:52.522
♪

19:08.451 --> 19:11.585
- He walked with me to church
the day after my dad died.

19:11.628 --> 19:13.500
Said he'd always
take care of me.

19:15.110 --> 19:17.634
I was supposed to take care
of him too.

19:17.678 --> 19:18.983
- The man loves you.

19:22.552 --> 19:24.250
- Hey, do you remember
who showed up at the house

19:24.293 --> 19:25.599
after Dad died?

19:25.642 --> 19:27.253
- A lot of people
paid their respects.

19:27.296 --> 19:28.863
- Yeah, but does
anybody stick out?

19:28.906 --> 19:30.778
Like, anybody ever
come by the station

19:30.821 --> 19:32.345
asking for Earl's things?

19:32.388 --> 19:34.303
- No.

19:35.130 --> 19:37.872
Cabin burned down
a couple weeks after he passed.

19:37.915 --> 19:40.396
Figured it's just
some kids camping nearby.

19:40.440 --> 19:43.312
Forgot to put the fire out.
Tossed a lit cigarette.

19:43.356 --> 19:45.532
No way to know
if anything was taken.

19:45.575 --> 19:47.577
- What about Edie Poole?

19:47.621 --> 19:49.013
Anybody show up
asking about her?

19:49.057 --> 19:50.537
- No.

19:53.714 --> 19:56.586
But she did report a break-in
a few days later.

19:56.630 --> 19:58.501
Nothing was taken.

19:58.545 --> 20:00.329
I just never thought
anything of it.

20:00.373 --> 20:02.026
Pooles ran with a rough crowd.

20:02.070 --> 20:03.854
- It wasn't the Pooles.

20:03.898 --> 20:06.466
[heart monitor beeping]

20:06.509 --> 20:09.469
[dramatic music]

20:09.512 --> 20:12.776
♪

20:12.820 --> 20:15.475
- What are you doing?

20:15.518 --> 20:17.738
- Just checking his levels.
Adjusting his dosage.

20:17.781 --> 20:19.479
- Is that something
that orderlies do now?

20:19.522 --> 20:20.741
- We're short-staffed.

20:20.784 --> 20:22.786
Sometimes I handle
other duties.

20:22.830 --> 20:24.092
- Yeah, stop.

20:25.180 --> 20:27.835
[both grunting]

20:27.878 --> 20:31.708
♪

20:31.752 --> 20:33.536
Bob Lee.
Bob Lee!

20:33.580 --> 20:36.017
Hey, that orderly,
I think he tried to kill Sam!

20:36.060 --> 20:37.671
He ran that way!

20:37.714 --> 20:44.765
♪

20:50.118 --> 20:51.554
- Ah!
[objects crash]

20:51.598 --> 20:58.692
♪

21:14.229 --> 21:17.972
[tires squealing]

21:18.015 --> 21:19.713
- Shit!

21:24.239 --> 21:24.370
.

21:24.413 --> 21:26.415
- Hospital said the temp
agency recommended him.

21:26.459 --> 21:28.069
All done via email.

21:28.112 --> 21:29.505
Wasn't lying about
the short-staffed part.

21:29.549 --> 21:30.811
- Let me guess.
The temp agency is gone now.

21:30.854 --> 21:32.334
- If it ever existed.

21:32.378 --> 21:34.989
Deputy just told me they
ransacked Sam's office too.

21:35.032 --> 21:36.860
Must mean they're
running out of time.

21:36.904 --> 21:39.298
- Whatever this evidence is,
Atlas is convinced

21:39.341 --> 21:42.344
it's still around,
and Sam knows where it is.

21:42.388 --> 21:44.955
- You said your dad
only cared about two things:

21:44.999 --> 21:46.348
work and work.

21:48.045 --> 21:49.917
- Besides Jimmy Poole,
was there any other case

21:49.960 --> 21:52.223
Dad was working on
when he died?

21:52.267 --> 21:54.182
It's worth a shot.

22:00.406 --> 22:03.365
- We don't use Craigslist
anymore to set these meets.

22:03.409 --> 22:05.367
- I know.
That's why I used it.

22:05.411 --> 22:08.849
I don't need any prying eyes.
- What do you want?

22:08.892 --> 22:10.329
- Get me off that list.

22:11.242 --> 22:12.331
- I can't.

22:16.247 --> 22:19.207
- You want the decrypter,
right?

22:19.250 --> 22:21.035
- Why now?
- Because when this ends,

22:21.078 --> 22:22.863
I want to be
on the winning side.

22:22.906 --> 22:24.168
And I want to be free.

22:25.648 --> 22:28.477
- There's not a place in
the world they won't find you.

22:28.521 --> 22:30.436
- They won't look
if you tell them not to.

22:30.479 --> 22:32.263
They need you.

22:34.004 --> 22:35.397
- You're overestimating
my power.

22:35.441 --> 22:36.529
- I'm only on that list

22:36.572 --> 22:38.052
because I ran
covert protection

22:38.095 --> 22:39.401
for Red Bama at Ag.

22:39.445 --> 22:42.273
They're worried
I saw something I didn't.

22:45.451 --> 22:46.626
- Do you have the card?

22:48.454 --> 22:50.934
- Give me 48 hours.

22:56.418 --> 22:59.160
[gunshot]

23:01.336 --> 23:03.425
- High and to the left,
but you hit it.

23:03.469 --> 23:05.427
Not bad from 800 yards.

23:07.081 --> 23:08.952
- You finally gonna tell me
about what you do?

23:10.214 --> 23:12.086
- How much you think
you already know?

23:13.087 --> 23:17.396
- I know it's a lot more
than most government employees.

23:17.439 --> 23:21.051
I figured CIA.
- Hmm.

23:22.488 --> 23:24.620
A little more
complicated than that.

23:30.147 --> 23:33.150
[soft dramatic music]

23:33.194 --> 23:36.240
30 years ago, I did a favor.

23:36.284 --> 23:39.548
♪

23:39.592 --> 23:42.943
I helped remove a traitor.

23:42.986 --> 23:44.684
[gunshot]

23:44.727 --> 23:46.555
♪

23:46.599 --> 23:48.470
- Earl Swagger.

23:48.514 --> 23:49.602
[gun clicking]

23:49.645 --> 23:53.040
[shell clatters]

23:53.083 --> 23:54.998
- Success with that

23:55.042 --> 23:58.654
led to an invitation
to join this group.

23:58.698 --> 24:01.352
I was the 11th member.

24:01.396 --> 24:05.444
We were an organization of
individuals with unique skills,

24:05.487 --> 24:09.056
applying them when
and where we needed

24:09.099 --> 24:10.623
to keep the country
and the world

24:10.666 --> 24:12.494
moving in the same direction.

24:12.538 --> 24:14.409
No fanfare, no medals.

24:16.063 --> 24:18.500
- That's what you meant about
the door being one-way only.

24:18.544 --> 24:21.372
- That's right, son.

24:21.416 --> 24:23.549
And once you enter,

24:23.592 --> 24:26.552
I can be of no further help,
no matter what.

24:26.595 --> 24:27.770
You understand that?

24:27.814 --> 24:28.771
- Yes.
- Red--

24:28.815 --> 24:31.252
- Dad.

24:31.295 --> 24:35.648
I've waited my entire life
to be a part of what you do.

24:35.691 --> 24:38.564
I know this is who I am.
Please.

24:38.607 --> 24:41.523
♪

24:41.567 --> 24:43.438
- Since this is
the official record,

24:43.482 --> 24:46.267
I want to say...

24:46.310 --> 24:49.575
that I served my country
as proudly as I knew how.

24:49.618 --> 24:53.579
Vietnam was, uh...

24:53.622 --> 24:55.798
a mess.

24:55.842 --> 24:59.715
Lots of us found ourselves
in situations that couldn't

24:59.759 --> 25:01.195
and, uh...

25:01.238 --> 25:03.197
♪

25:03.240 --> 25:05.199
And still can't
be described

25:05.242 --> 25:07.201
except to say
they were horrible.

25:07.244 --> 25:10.291
♪

25:10.334 --> 25:12.598
It's been over an hour.

25:12.641 --> 25:15.514
- It isn't the railroad.
They don't always run on time.

25:15.557 --> 25:17.733
- Your contact said 1400.

25:17.777 --> 25:21.389
♪

25:21.432 --> 25:23.347
- So he was wrong.

25:23.391 --> 25:25.698
♪

25:25.741 --> 25:27.047
- Who is he?

25:27.090 --> 25:29.049
- [scoffs]
God damn it, Swagger.

25:29.092 --> 25:30.224
The mission's the mission.

25:30.267 --> 25:33.053
You always ask
this many questions?

25:33.096 --> 25:35.577
- I do when it don't
feel right.

25:35.621 --> 25:36.578
- Here we go.

25:36.622 --> 25:39.799
- Hey.
- Hey.

25:39.842 --> 25:46.501
♪

25:55.466 --> 25:57.425
- LaFort.

25:57.468 --> 26:00.167
That name mean anything to you?

26:00.210 --> 26:03.605
- No, nothing in particular.
Why?

26:03.649 --> 26:06.390
- My dad had a tic.

26:06.434 --> 26:08.262
He'd make me repeat
the same thing three times

26:08.305 --> 26:10.264
so I knew it was important.

26:10.307 --> 26:12.701
He underlined that name
three times.

26:12.745 --> 26:14.485
- Could be nothing.

26:16.313 --> 26:18.489
But according to these notes,
this was a simple

26:18.533 --> 26:19.839
no-fault car accident.

26:19.882 --> 26:22.624
It was open and shut.

26:22.668 --> 26:24.365
I think he's trying
to send a message.

26:24.408 --> 26:27.281
Could be where he hid
the evidence.

26:27.324 --> 26:28.674
Where's the case file?

26:28.717 --> 26:30.501
- All these files
are in Fort Worth

26:30.545 --> 26:32.329
in the state records.

26:42.252 --> 26:44.907
- Swagger's got a lead
on his dad's evidence.

26:44.951 --> 26:46.648
- How?

26:46.692 --> 26:50.173
- Had a man at the hospital
with Mr. Vincent.

26:50.217 --> 26:52.393
Your son told him
what you were looking for.

26:52.436 --> 26:54.525
Vincent told Swagger.

26:54.569 --> 26:57.833
If he gets it and it reveals
what we fear it reveals,

26:57.877 --> 26:59.879
this will all have been
for nothing.

26:59.922 --> 27:02.882
30 years of work, poof, gone.

27:02.925 --> 27:04.797
- What do you want me to do?

27:06.407 --> 27:10.411
- Let me ask you.
Why did you join us?

27:12.718 --> 27:16.504
- Because I believed
in what you told us,

27:16.547 --> 27:20.900
that our country is greater
than ourselves, that...

27:20.943 --> 27:25.731
that our free society depends
on controlling world events,

27:25.774 --> 27:28.864
that sometimes the price
of freedom is paid in blood.

27:28.908 --> 27:32.172
- Do you still believe that?
- Dedicated my life to it.

27:32.215 --> 27:34.348
- And if our mission
were to be threatened

27:34.391 --> 27:37.220
the way Earl Swagger did
30 years ago,

27:37.264 --> 27:38.831
what would you do?

27:38.874 --> 27:42.573
[dramatic music]

27:42.617 --> 27:43.836
- No.

27:43.879 --> 27:46.273
- Everyone saw you
bring him here.

27:46.316 --> 27:47.404
- No.

27:47.448 --> 27:48.449
- And soon everyone will know

27:48.492 --> 27:49.711
it was his mistake

27:49.755 --> 27:53.497
that might cost us
everything.

27:53.541 --> 27:54.716
- You can't be
asking me to do this.

27:54.760 --> 27:55.848
He's my son.

27:55.891 --> 27:57.545
- I can have
someone else do it,

27:57.588 --> 27:58.851
but it needs to be done--

27:58.894 --> 28:02.898
not as a punishment,
as an example

28:02.942 --> 28:06.423
of how deep our belief is.

28:06.467 --> 28:09.949
♪

28:09.992 --> 28:12.952
You brought him here
for a reason, Red.

28:12.995 --> 28:15.389
It sure as hell
wasn't to join up.

28:15.432 --> 28:16.999
You and I both know
he wouldn't get through

28:17.043 --> 28:19.567
day one of training.

28:19.610 --> 28:23.876
I suspect you knew
it would come to this.

28:23.919 --> 28:28.315
For what it's worth,
I'm sorry.

28:28.358 --> 28:35.452
♪

28:43.765 --> 28:43.983
.

28:44.026 --> 28:47.116
- Man, they got cases
going back 50 years.

28:47.160 --> 28:49.640
- Yeah, this will all
get scanned eventually.

28:49.684 --> 28:51.730
I guess they aren't
in much of a rush.

28:55.864 --> 28:58.171
- Getting closer.

29:00.826 --> 29:02.958
Found it.

29:03.002 --> 29:06.179
Case files from '87, '88.

29:17.233 --> 29:19.105
This is it.
This is the evidence.

29:19.148 --> 29:23.674
[power shutting down]

29:23.718 --> 29:25.067
- Maybe it's on a timer.

29:25.111 --> 29:27.896
- You and I both know
it's not a timer.

29:27.940 --> 29:29.811
They must have tailed us.

29:29.855 --> 29:31.334
- Are they really gonna get
into a shoot-out

29:31.378 --> 29:33.902
in a police records facility?

29:33.946 --> 29:35.382
- This is what they're after.

29:35.425 --> 29:37.863
[dramatic music]

29:37.906 --> 29:41.040
- Shit.
They're jamming the phones.

29:41.083 --> 29:43.912
- Until we know
what's on this tape,

29:43.956 --> 29:45.174
we're gonna get out
of here quietly.

29:45.218 --> 29:47.046
- All right, let's split up.

29:47.089 --> 29:48.699
Worst case,
I draw their attention.

29:48.743 --> 29:50.832
You get to a phone.
- Don't get killed.

29:50.876 --> 29:52.442
- Wasn't planning on it.

29:52.486 --> 29:59.754
♪

30:40.490 --> 30:42.797
- [grunts]
[gunshot]

30:42.841 --> 30:47.933
♪

30:47.976 --> 30:51.850
[both grunting]

30:51.893 --> 30:58.944
♪

31:19.965 --> 31:21.270
[gunshot]

31:21.314 --> 31:26.058
♪

31:26.101 --> 31:28.930
- [grunting]

31:28.974 --> 31:36.068
♪

31:44.424 --> 31:45.555
- You hit?

31:47.166 --> 31:48.428
- What the hell
are you doing here?

31:48.471 --> 31:50.343
I'm trying to draw them away.

31:50.386 --> 31:52.998
[gunshots]
[man grunting]

31:55.174 --> 31:57.959
Goddamn.
- Let's go.

31:58.003 --> 32:00.266
They can explain to the cops
what they're doing here.

32:06.576 --> 32:08.317
- Hey.

32:08.361 --> 32:10.363
Oh, come on.
Is that what I think it is?

32:12.539 --> 32:15.368
- Been saving this
for a special occasion.

32:15.411 --> 32:19.459
- Holy shit.
I'm in?

32:22.592 --> 32:24.986
- I talked
to the man in charge.

32:25.030 --> 32:26.988
You start your training
next week.

32:27.032 --> 32:30.035
- [laughs]

32:33.603 --> 32:35.301
Wow.

32:40.306 --> 32:41.394
[sighs]

32:43.613 --> 32:46.312
So when do I meet
this man in charge?

32:50.098 --> 32:52.448
- His name is August Russo.

32:52.492 --> 32:55.016
And soon.

32:55.060 --> 32:56.409
- What's he like?

32:57.540 --> 33:00.326
- Righteous.

33:00.369 --> 33:02.545
A visionary.

33:02.589 --> 33:05.374
Hung on to the belief
that a...

33:05.418 --> 33:10.553
small, dedicated
group of people

33:10.597 --> 33:14.253
willing to do
the hard thing...

33:14.296 --> 33:17.430
could guide this nation
through some dark days.

33:18.648 --> 33:20.172
- Damn.

33:20.215 --> 33:21.956
I wish I could have been there
when it started.

33:25.090 --> 33:27.918
- Things were simpler then.

33:27.962 --> 33:29.529
- I know I've made mistakes.

33:31.487 --> 33:34.969
Thank you...
for giving me a chance.

33:35.013 --> 33:39.321
You always believed in me.
And I will not let you down.

33:44.544 --> 33:46.067
- I know.

33:46.111 --> 33:47.982
- Can't believe
it worked out in the end.

33:48.026 --> 33:53.422
Me and you,
working together for real.

33:53.466 --> 33:55.424
I can't wait to get started.

33:55.468 --> 33:58.427
[somber music]

33:58.471 --> 34:04.129
♪

34:04.172 --> 34:07.262
- I'm proud of you, boy.

34:07.306 --> 34:08.655
Know that.

34:08.698 --> 34:11.571
- I do, Dad.

34:11.614 --> 34:13.181
I do.

34:13.225 --> 34:20.319
♪

34:36.248 --> 34:38.032
- Get some sleep.

34:40.556 --> 34:44.125
[line trilling]

34:44.169 --> 34:45.518
- Hey.

34:45.561 --> 34:48.216
- Hey, I was calling you.
- I got it.

34:48.260 --> 34:51.089
I found my dad's evidence.

34:51.132 --> 34:53.743
- Listen, Bob Lee, uh...

34:53.787 --> 34:56.485
the poison didn't enter
Sam's bloodstream.

34:57.747 --> 34:59.619
But he took a turn
for the worse.

35:01.490 --> 35:02.665
I'm sorry.

35:02.709 --> 35:05.233
[dramatic music]

35:05.277 --> 35:06.669
I'm so sorry.

35:06.713 --> 35:13.807
♪

35:26.689 --> 35:29.649
- [crying]

35:29.692 --> 35:36.743
♪

35:43.750 --> 35:46.622
I don't know if you
can hear me right now

35:46.666 --> 35:50.235
wherever you are.

35:50.278 --> 35:54.282
But I just want to say thanks.
Thank you, Sam.

35:54.326 --> 35:57.546
♪

35:57.590 --> 35:59.157
Thanks for helping Mom.

35:59.200 --> 36:01.550
♪

36:01.594 --> 36:03.639
Thanks for looking out for me.

36:03.683 --> 36:07.165
♪

36:07.208 --> 36:08.514
I hope I made you proud.

36:08.557 --> 36:12.605
♪

36:12.648 --> 36:16.217
And I know you wouldn't like me
sitting here crying like this,

36:16.261 --> 36:18.785
but...tough shit.

36:18.828 --> 36:21.483
♪

36:21.527 --> 36:23.311
I miss you already.

36:23.355 --> 36:30.318
♪

36:30.362 --> 36:33.408
You were always there, Sam.

36:33.452 --> 36:35.410
I never had
to worry about that.

36:35.454 --> 36:38.239
♪

36:38.283 --> 36:41.242
That's more than I can say
for my actual father.

36:41.286 --> 36:45.594
♪

36:45.638 --> 36:47.205
And I love you.

36:53.689 --> 36:53.907
.

36:53.950 --> 36:57.040
[insects chirping,
birds calling]

36:57.084 --> 37:00.043
[dramatic music]

37:00.087 --> 37:07.181
♪

37:34.252 --> 37:36.384
- She finally went to sleep.

37:38.386 --> 37:39.996
She asked me if she could
say all her prayers

37:40.040 --> 37:41.346
tonight for Sam.

37:43.043 --> 37:44.349
- Sweet girl.

37:47.439 --> 37:50.355
- What are you gonna do
about Junior?

37:50.398 --> 37:51.965
- I don't know yet.

37:53.358 --> 37:56.099
But I'm gonna do something.

37:56.143 --> 37:58.058
- Did you find anything here?

37:58.101 --> 37:59.320
- Yeah, actually.

37:59.364 --> 38:02.454
The Vietnam case files
are really detailed.

38:02.497 --> 38:07.067
And once I can get my hands
on a VCR, I'll know more.

38:09.243 --> 38:12.290
You know, if you guys
weren't pressing the Bamas,

38:12.333 --> 38:15.075
I never would have found this.

38:15.118 --> 38:17.033
- Just hope it's worth it.

38:21.516 --> 38:22.909
I need to go to bed.

38:25.128 --> 38:26.956
Don't stay up too late, okay?

38:27.000 --> 38:28.088
- All right.

38:37.315 --> 38:44.365
♪

38:45.975 --> 38:47.412
- Who's running you?

38:50.284 --> 38:51.416
Who's running you?

38:52.939 --> 38:54.288
- They may not speak English,
Major.

38:54.332 --> 38:56.029
I mean, we are deep
in the bush here.

38:56.072 --> 38:58.771
- Well, thanks for
the geography lesson, Swagger.

39:01.339 --> 39:03.341
- Let's see
what's in the truck.

39:03.384 --> 39:06.735
- Why don't you and your men
take up defensive positions?

39:06.779 --> 39:09.303
I'll handle this.

39:09.347 --> 39:11.218
- This is my team, Brooks.

39:11.261 --> 39:13.394
♪

39:13.438 --> 39:15.309
- I gave you an order.

39:15.353 --> 39:22.360
♪
♪

39:23.578 --> 39:25.537
- You said they were
running weapons.

39:25.580 --> 39:29.497
♪

39:29.541 --> 39:31.369
What is this?
Dope?

39:31.412 --> 39:33.283
- The future.

39:33.327 --> 39:35.285
Leave it and walk away.

39:35.329 --> 39:38.288
We'll discuss your transfer out
of my group when we get back.

39:38.332 --> 39:39.812
♪

39:39.855 --> 39:41.379
I'm done with this.

39:41.422 --> 39:44.817
Count of three, I want
to know who your boss is.

39:44.860 --> 39:46.427
And cut the "no English" shit.

39:46.471 --> 39:49.212
♪

39:49.256 --> 39:51.040
One.
- Jesus, Brooks.

39:51.084 --> 39:53.129
- Two.
- Jesus, Brooks!

39:53.173 --> 39:54.130
[gunshot]
- What the hell's wrong

39:54.174 --> 39:55.567
with you?
- Three.

39:55.610 --> 39:58.004
- What the hell are you doing?
[women screaming]

39:58.047 --> 39:59.135
- He's an enemy.

39:59.179 --> 40:00.267
- Get your head
out of your ass.

40:00.310 --> 40:01.921
We're all accomplices now.

40:01.964 --> 40:03.836
- Well, you know
what they say, Swagger.

40:03.879 --> 40:07.143
Three people can keep a secret
if two are dead.

40:07.187 --> 40:08.493
[gunshot]

40:09.450 --> 40:11.278
- God damn it.

40:12.192 --> 40:15.108
- Get that gun
out of my face, Sergeant.

40:15.151 --> 40:18.328
♪

40:18.372 --> 40:20.156
- My team isn't a part of this.

40:20.200 --> 40:25.031
♪

40:25.074 --> 40:26.467
[both grunt]

40:26.511 --> 40:28.948
♪

40:28.991 --> 40:32.908
You can find your own way home.

40:32.952 --> 40:36.259
♪

40:36.303 --> 40:38.348
- And I know the president
would be saying

40:38.392 --> 40:41.047
the same thing now
if he were here.

40:41.090 --> 40:43.310
Ladies and gentlemen,
our next chief justice

40:43.353 --> 40:46.835
of the Supreme Court,
Ray Brooks.

40:46.879 --> 40:51.100
[applause]

40:51.144 --> 40:53.451
- It is with great humility
and respect that I accept

40:53.494 --> 40:55.888
the president's invitation
that I serve our country

40:55.931 --> 40:57.324
one last time.

40:57.367 --> 40:59.500
I hope to live up
to the exacting standards

40:59.544 --> 41:03.069
that our great nation
lays in front of me.

41:03.112 --> 41:05.506
I look forward
to the confirmation hearings.

41:05.550 --> 41:07.247
Thank you all.

41:07.290 --> 41:08.857
[applause]

41:08.901 --> 41:11.251
- Good work.

41:11.294 --> 41:13.122
- His name is Ray Brooks.

41:13.166 --> 41:14.994
He was a major when I knew him.

41:15.037 --> 41:16.386
But two months ago,
he was appointed

41:16.430 --> 41:18.171
to the federal appellate.

41:18.214 --> 41:20.042
♪

41:20.086 --> 41:22.871
I've done some research.

41:22.915 --> 41:24.525
Brooks has quietly
been working his way up

41:24.569 --> 41:28.398
from DA
to attorney general of Utah

41:28.442 --> 41:30.313
and now the federal bench.

41:30.357 --> 41:32.402
All of his elections,
his actions,

41:32.446 --> 41:35.231
his cases reek of Atlas.

41:35.275 --> 41:37.233
Whatever it is
they're planning...

41:37.277 --> 41:39.148
♪

41:39.192 --> 41:41.107
It won't end

41:41.150 --> 41:43.936
until someone stops them.
